    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1966-07-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1966-07-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="622"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                <head>622. Memorandum Prepared by the President’s Special Assistant (<persName
                        type="to">Rostow</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d622fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>-<gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files: Lot 72 D 318, July 14, 1966.
                        Confidential. Filed with a covering memorandum to the Secretaries of State,
                        Treasury, and Defense, the <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>
                        Administrator, <gloss target="#t_USIA1">USIA</gloss> Director, and Director
                        of Central Intelligence.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1966-07-14">July 14, 1966</date>. </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following the National Security Council meeting today, the President asked the
                    Secretary of State to set up a task force on the South West Africa problem
                    composed of those officers in State, Defense, <gloss target="#t_AID1"
                        >AID</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_USIA1">USIA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CIA1"
                        >CIA</gloss>, and the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Staff, who are
                    primarily responsible for African Affairs.</p>
                <p>The task force is to prepare: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>a suggested U.S. statement for use immediately following the court
                            decision;</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>a short term “holding” position to permit us time to assess the
                            decision and reactions to it at home, in Africa and among our
                            allies;</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>a longer-range plan for dealing with this issue in Africa, in the
                            Western alliance, in the East-West arena and in the <gloss
                                target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The task force is to work closely with Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_GAJ1"
                        >Goldberg</persName> and his staff.</p>
                <p>The task force should establish and maintain close relations with those members
                    of Congress and their staff who are interested in African problems.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">W.W. Rostow</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
